  return (0.5*(x+x^2))
}

  return (x+0.5)
}

fy<-function(x){
  return((2/3)*(1+x))
}
inverse_G <- function(y){ #cdf
  return ((3*(y+1/3))^0.5-1)
}

#2(b) Fxinverse functionFx-a=0ay0<a<1)aunirootxauni(0,1)10000x

Fx<-function(x){
  return (1-exp(-x)-exp(-2*x)+exp(-3*x))
}
f <- function(x,a){
  return (1-exp(-x)-exp(-2*x)+exp(-3*x)-a)
}

U1<-runif(10000,0,1)
vec = numeric(10000)
for(i in 1:10000){
  root<-uniroot(f,interval = c(0,100),a = U1[i])$root
  vec[i]<-root
}

generatecdfcdf

plot(ecdf(vec)) 
lines(seq(0,max(vec),length.out = 100),Fx(seq(0,max(vec),length.out = 100)),col="red")

#3(b) Composition Method pdf3distribution g1,g2,g30.250.50.25 g2,g3 cdfinverse functioninverse_G2inverse_G3 g1=1cdf inverseuni(0,1)

g1<- function(x){
  return(1)
}
g2 <- function(x){
  return(4*x^3)
}
g3 <- function(x){
  return(5*x^4)
}
inverse_G2<-function(y){
  return(y^(0.25))
}
inverse_G3<-function(y){
  return(y^(0.2))
}

U1uni(0,1) vec 0<=U1<0.25vec0uni(0,1)g1=1uni(0,1) 0.25<=U1<0.75vec0g2 0.75<=U1<0.1vec0g3

U1<-runif(10000,0,1)
vec = numeric(10000)
for(i in 1:10000){
  if(0<=U1[i] &&U1[i]<0.25){
    vec[i] = runif(1,0,1)
  }else if(0.25<=U1[i] &&U1[i]<0.75){
    vec[i] = inverse_G2(runif(1,0,1))
  }else{
    vec[i] = inverse_G3(runif(1,0,1))
  }
}

composition method cdf function cdf

plot(ecdf(vec)) 
lines(seq(0,1,length.out = 100),Fx(seq(0,1,length.out = 100)),col="red")
